    "original_source_path": "newapp/dataset=decision/decision/commonwealth/1992/decision_commonwealth_1992_caf4830a.json",
    "text": "It is of course well established that an appellate court will not grant leave to appeal from an interlocutory order unless it is satisfied that there is both an error and the likelihood of injustice if the error is not corrected. In our view, no error has been demonstrated in this case.",
